  "description": [
    "FOUR Fled Italy to Save Flag of Hope Political RevivalTurati LIFE WAS NOT MENACED SAYS AGED SOCIALIST Must Organize Against Fascism From Outside Now Trader Special Service PARlSFilippo Turati leader of the moderates in the Italian Social ist party who recently fled from Italy to France writes in an article in Le Soir a Faris evening paper that he did not leave Mussolini land because he was afraid to be mur dered Life cannot mean much to an old man of 70 years who had to watch Mussolini destroy the work of 50 years of Italian Socialist effort Tu rati explains There is no hope for Socialists in Italy under Mussolini There is no freedom of thought of the press of speech nor even an open forum in parliament Fascists Guarded Turati Fascism did not menace him per sonally Turati goes on The Fascist police insulted him with their pro toction against the blackshirts of the Fascist regime Maybe they wanted to keep him as a hostage or they considered foreign opinion lie came to France the classic land of revolution and freedom Turati declared in order to save the flag of hope of political revival and of revenge AH"
  ],
